  "chapter": {
    "number": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Rulers and Prophets Condemned"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then I said:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Hear now, O leaders of Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you rulers of the house of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Should you not know justice?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You hate good and love evil.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You tear the skin from my people",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and strip the flesh from their bones.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You eat the flesh of my people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "after stripping off their skin",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and breaking their bones.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You chop them up like flesh for the cooking pot,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like meat in a cauldron.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then they will cry out to the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but He will not answer them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "At that time He will hide His face from them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because of the evil they have done.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "This is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“As for the prophets",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who lead My people astray,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who proclaim peace",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "while they chew with their teeth,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but declare war against one",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who puts nothing in their mouths:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore night will come over you without visions,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and darkness without divination.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The sun will set on these prophets,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the daylight will turn black over them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the seers will be ashamed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the diviners will be disgraced.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will all cover their mouths",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because there is no answer from God.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As for me, however, I am filled with power",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "by the Spirit of the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with justice and courage,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to declare to Jacob his transgression",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and to Israel his sin.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Now hear this, O leaders of the house of Jacob",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and rulers of the house of Israel,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who despise justice",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and pervert all that is right,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who build Zion with bloodshed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Jerusalem with iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Her leaders judge for a bribe,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "her priests teach for a price,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and her prophets practice divination for money.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Yet they lean upon the LORD, saying,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Is not the LORD among us?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "No disaster can come upon us.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, because of you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Zion will be plowed like a field,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Jerusalem will become a heap of rubble,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the temple mount a wooded ridge.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
  },
